headline: DGX Q4 Deep Dive: Consumer Testing and Advanced Diagnostics Fuel Growth Amid Margin Headwinds
summary: Healthcare diagnostics company Quest Diagnostics (NYSE:DGX) reported Q4 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 7.1% year on year to $2.81 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $11.76 billion at the midpoint came in 3.3% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.42 per share was 2.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
